vibesExplanation:

The interval format, along with the climb structure and moderately high rhythm of 30, point towards 'The Endorphin Wave.' This vibe signifies an elevated, feel-good movement with a steady build, justified by the consistent effort over four-minute intervals, scored at 0.75.

Additionally, the focus on rowing and repetition aligns with 'The Meditative Grind', which emphasizes zoned-in endurance. The integration of rock and global hits provides energetic and engaging accompaniment, justifying a score of 0.65.

The workout's medium intensity (level 2 out of 3) and its inherent nod to empowerment and celebration minimize the fit for high-intensity vibes, with no extreme challenges or speed elements noted.
